    "notes": "To protect your GraphQL API from overly complex or expensive queries, you can limit the query depth. This helps prevent performance issues and potential abuse. You can set a maximum query depth in two places: At the Policy level, which applies to all keys associated with that policy.\u000b Or at the individual API Key level, for more granular control.\u000b Setting these limits ensures your API stays performant and secure by restricting how deeply clients can nest their queries."
